title: Panel, 1900–69
medium:
Medium: cotton
Technique: wax resist dyeing (batik) on plain weave
description: Batik textile showing three wayang puppet figures (traditional flat cut-out and pierced leather puppets) in typical attitudes. Two face each other and the other away, each in different manner of dress. Medium blue and dark brown on ivory cotton fabric. The ground is dark brown.
